<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1924-09-29T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1924-09-29T17:00:00-05:00" n="630" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d630">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">839.6463/168: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in the Dominican Republic</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Russell</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1924-09-29T17:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">September 29,
                                        1924—5 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>37. Your 56, September 26, 5 p.m.</p>
                        <p>Department informed by Hunt and Dominican Minister that on September 25,
                            they signed the contract of sale of the Santo Domingo <pb facs="0799" n="685" xml:id="pg_685"/> Water, Light &amp; Power Company’s
                            properties to the Dominican Government. The terms of this contract are
                            in accordance with statement in your telegram.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>